Macquarie University will finance two PhD candidate scholarships (MQRES) =
associated with the Australian Research Council Discovery Grant =
DP130101969 in the subject area:

Mathematics - Structural homotopy theory: a category theoretic study.

The Chief Investigators of the Grant are=20
Ross Street, Dominic Verity, Stephen Lack and Richard Garner.
The PhD candidates would be supervised by one or two of us.

More details and how to apply can be found at the Australia-wide page

<http://www.jason.edu.au/scholarship.pl?id=3D6280&page=3D1>

and the Macquarie University Higher Degree Research page

=
<http://www.hdr.mq.edu.au/information_about/scholarships/hdr_scholarships_=
domestic_and_international>.

There is a closing date of 7 March 2013 for applications.

The 2013 MQRES full-time stipend rate is $24,653 pa tax exempt for 3.5 =
years.

Applicants will need to complete a candidature/scholarship application =
form and arrange for two academic referee reports to be submitted to the =
Higher Degree Research Office. Refer to the Applications page for =
further application instructions. Macquarie University will advise the =
successful applicant of entitlements at the time of scholarship offer.

Please quote the allocation reference number 2013081 & 2013082 on your =
application.

Best wishes,
Ross Street


